Notes.Title: Microkernels and Essential Services
Notes.Content: Microkernels are designed to provide three essential services: Process Management, Memory Management (虚拟 memory), and Inter-Process Communication (IPC). They primarily offer a message passing mechanism and execute services in user mode. Examples of additional, non-essential services include disk management, file management, I/O subsystems, and security.

They primarily offer a message passing method overview and execute services in user mode. Examples of additional, non-essential services include disk management, file management, I/O subsystem, and protection.
